name.text: Japanese Calligraphy Beginner Course (Fall 2019)
name.html: Japanese Calligraphy Beginner Course (Fall 2019)

description.text:
WHEN: 8 Tuesdays from October 1st to November 19th, 2019 
TIME: 6:30pm - 8:00pm
WHERE: 2305 West 7th Avenue V6K 1Y4, Vancouver BC
SIGN UP: kisyuu-calligraphy.com
This 8-week course will be perfect for those who want to study deeper than what is provided in the Workshop and improve both your writing skills and the balance between mind and body.
During eight weeks, we will go over the basics of Japanese calligraphy, including:


About the four-treasures of calligraphy tools (brush, ink, paper & ink stone case)


Meditation practice while making sumi-ink


How to hold the brush and control big & small brushes


Eight fundamental brush strokes for formal regular script, "Kaisho" style


How to write kanji and hiragana (Japanese alphabets)


Practice and create your own calligraphy artwork


Experience both traditional and modern calligraphy writing



*Everybody is welcome – no prior art experience or Japanese language skills are necessary!
*Students will be required to bring their own equipment. In the case that students do not own equipment, basic calligraphy kits can be purchased from Kisyuu at cost.
*Maximum number of participant is 7. Register soon!

Potential Schedule for the course:
Week 1 : Brush & Horizontal LineWeek 2 : Horizontal Line & Vertical LineWeek 3 : Long Tails – Left & RightWeek 4 : Dots & Big Brush ChallengeWeek 5 : Name Writing & Small Brush ChallengeWeek 6 : Review & Eiji HappoWeek 7 : HiraganaWeek 8 : Create Your Own Calligraphy Art
